article.description: Eric Monroe had 15 points as Yale beat Dartmouth 72-61 on Friday night.
article.headline: Monroe scores 15 to lead Yale over Dartmouth 72-61
article.linkText: Monroe scores 15 to lead Yale over Dartmouth 72-61
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Eric Monroe had 15 points as Yale beat Dartmouth 72-61 on Friday night. Monroe made 5 of 7 3-pointers. Paul Atkinson had 14 points for Yale (23-6, 11-2 Ivy League), which earned its fifth consecutive victory. Azar Swain added 14 points. Jordan Bruner had 11 rebounds. Aaryn Rai had 18 points for the Big Green (12-16, 5-8). Chris Knight added 17 points. James Foye had six rebounds. The Bulldogs improve to 2-0 against the Big Green this season. Yale defeated Dartmouth 75-57 on Feb. 8. Yale finishes out the regular season against Harvard on the road on Saturday. Dartmouth finishes out the regular season against Brown at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
